playerctl (mpris media player controller and lib for spotify, vlc, 
audacious, bmp, xmms2, and others.)

Playerctl is a command-line utility and library for controlling media players 
that implement the [MPRIS](http://specifications.freedesktop.org/mpris-spec/latest/) 
D-Bus Interface Specification. Playerctl makes it easy to bind player actions, 
such as play and pause, to media keys.


